results.name: a(n) = smallest non-palindromic number k such that the Reverse and Add! trajectory of k joins the trajectory of A089521(n).
comment: Terms of A063048 that are not terms of A088753 (not in ascending order). a(n) > A088753(n). a(n) is the substitute so to speak of A088753(n) in A063048.
a(12), a(15) to a(18), a(20), a(21) are conjectural; it is not yet ensured that they are minimal.
link: Index entries for sequences related to Reverse and Add!
example: The trajectories of A088753(1) = 9999 and of 19098 join at 2089791 and there is no number between 9999 and 19098 whose trajectory joins that of 9999.
results.author: _Klaus Brockhaus_, Nov 10 2003
